name: Mouse flowers
myth: Once there was a little mouse. She was born in a cozy little nook in the wall of a crawlspace with her brothers and sisters. As spring came, she and her siblings peeked their little noses out of a crack in the wall and set out on their own to explore. It was a beautiful world, scented with grass and lavender, alive with ants and ladybugs. The little mouse spent the whole summer roaming across every inch of the yard, sampling every scent and texture. It was a beautiful life. She watched every afternoon as the sun dipped a little lower in the sky, it's hue more golden by the day, until a chill started to settle into the edges of even the brightest moments. She new it was time to start building her winter nest, but something held her back. She wanted to find a seed from the most perfect flower to leave behind, so that next year's little mouselings could peek their noses out into a world just as beautiful as the one she's been in awe of that spring. But when she looked around, there were no more flowers in bloom. She sniffed the ground for days, but still found nothing. One morning, as an icy foggy streamed through the birch overhead, her frozen paws came across something unexpected: a tiny brown seed. She didn't know what is was. A fruit tree? A weed? But she held it in her paw, and remembered every beautiful thing she had touched and buried it in the ground. It was a long cold winter. Most wild mice don't live longer than 8 or 9 months, and our little mouse was not an exception. But the next spring, there was a new white flower, with tiny petals, brilliant as sunlit fog. Every autumn it dies, scattering new seeds to the ground. But in the winter, if you look up into the night sky, you can see it blooming, bright and small and beautiful in a vast dark ocean.

name: The Cosmic Snack
myth:
In a galaxy not so far away, there lived a group of intergalactic foodies known as the Snackonauts. They traveled the universe in search of the ultimate snack, and their leader, Captain Cheesy, was obsessed with finding the perfect pizza.

One day, while exploring a distant planet, Captain Cheesy and his crew stumbled upon a legendary pizza known as the "Slice of Destiny." It was said that whoever took a bite would gain the power to create the most delicious snacks in the universe. However, the pizza was guarded by the fearsome Lord Veggie, a tyrant who believed that only healthy snacks should exist.

Determined to claim the Slice of Destiny, Captain Cheesy challenged Lord Veggie to a cook-off. The two faced off in an epic battle of culinary skills, with the fate of snacks hanging in the balance. As they cooked, the Snackonauts cheered, and the aroma of deliciousness filled the air.

In a twist of fate, Captain Cheesy accidentally spilled a secret ingredient‚Äîcosmic cheese‚Äîinto his pizza. The pizza erupted in a burst of flavor, dazzling everyone present. Lord Veggie, unable to resist the mouthwatering aroma, conceded defeat and declared that all snacks, healthy or not, deserved a place in the universe.

To commemorate this legendary cook-off, the Snackonauts created The Cosmic Snack constellation, forever reminding everyone that life is too short to skip dessert. Now, whenever you gaze at the night sky and see the pizza slice, it‚Äôs a call to gather your friends, grab some snacks, and celebrate the joy of good food and laughter!
